0the%20Government%20of%20the%20Russian%20Federation%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERussia's%20economic%20strength%20as%20an%20indicator%20of%20unrest%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20long-term%20financial%20impacts%20of%20the%20war%20remain%20to%20be%20seen%2C%20an%20expert%20on%20Russia%20says%20keeping%20control%20of%20the%20economy%20now%20is%20Putin's%20best%20bet%20at%20maintaining%20power%20and%20preventing%20the%20country's%20elite%20and%20civilians%20alike%20from%20turning%20on%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Robert%20English%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20international%20relations%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Southern%20California%2C%20who%20specializes%20in%20foreign%20policy%20and%20defense%20analysis%20of%20Russia%20and%20the%20former%20USSR%2C%20told%20Insider%20he's%20skeptical%20that%20mass%20disorder%20or%20protest%20will%20occur%20unless%20something%20%26quot%3Breally%20significant%26quot%3B%20changes%20in%20the%20Russian%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20but%20then%20%26quot%3Ball%20bets%20are%20off.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPutin%20is%20kind%20of%20an%20evil%20genius%20at%20having%20figured%20out%20how%20to%20keep%20his%20country%20sort%20of%20afloat%20and%2C%20I%20won't%20say%20satisfied%2C%20but%20not%20so%20deeply%20dissatisfied%20that%20it%20does%20descend%20into%20rebellion%2C%20and%20so%20that%20the%20military%20losses%20are%20sustainable%2C%26quot%3B%20English%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BBut%20as%20far%20as%20social%20stability%20and%20socioeconomic%20unrest%2C%20their%20current%20state%20tells%20us%20that%20the%20status%20quo%20is%20sustainable.%20That%20sounds%20terrible%20because%2C%20of%20course%2C%20Russia%20is%20chewing%20up%20its%20future%2C%20but%20I%20would%20say%20that%20for%20another%20year%20or%20so%20the%20regime%20can%20hang%20on%20and%20keep%20the%20dissatisfaction%20down.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20long%20as%20the%20country%20maintains%20some%20semblance%20of%20the%20status%20quo%20in%20the%20economy%2C%20English%20said%20he%20doesn't%20expect%20to%20see%20things%20changing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20it%20gets%20much%20worse%2C%20if%20they%20lose%20huge%20chunks%20of%20territory%2C%20if%20the%20military%20is%20sent%20reeling%20backwards%2C%20if%20many%20more%20are%20dying%2C%20then%20all%20bets%20are%20off.%20Then%20a%20lot%20could%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20English%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20it%20could%20change%20surprisingly%20quickly%2C%20as%20it%20always%20does.%20No%20one%20ever%20expects%20a%20coup%20or%20some%20kind%20of%20internal%20reshuffling%20right%20until%20it%20happens%2C%20and%20then%20in%20hindsight%2C%20it%20'oh%20it%20was%20inevitable.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20though%2C%20English%20said%20economic%20pain%20will%20make%20it%20impossible%20to%20keep%20civilians%20satisfied%20if%20they%20face%20a%20lack%20of%20essential%20supplies.%20Living%20standards%20will%20degrade%2C%20inflation%20will%20skyrocket%2C%20the%20value%20of%20the%20ruble%20will%20continue%20to%20drop%20%E2%80%94%20and%20%26quot%3Bthen%20it'll%20get%20difficult%26quot%3B%20for%20Putin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThen%20we%20might%20see%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1989%2F05%2F04%2Fworld%2Fafter-rash-of-wildcat-moves-soviets-admit-right-to-strike.html%5C%22%3EWildcat%3C%2Fa%3E%20kind%20of%20action%2C%20spontaneous%20civilian%20outbursts%2C%26quot%3B%20English%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20might%20see%20more%20emigration%2C%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nonproliferation.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fnpr%2Fmoody33.pdf%5C%22%3Ebrain%20drain%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20all%20of%20that%20will%20suddenly%20start%20spiraling.%20Then%2C%20once%20it%20starts%20snowballing%2C%20it%20won't%20stop.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvladimir-putin-russia-economy-war-keep-control-of-country