avoid%20migration%20agents.%20This%20incident%20follows%20a%20recent%20surge%20in%20migrant%20deaths%20in%20Mexico%20as%20migrants%20travel%20towards%20the%20US%20border.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fat-least-16-migrants-killed-29-injured-in-a-bus-crash-in-southern-mexico%2Farticleshow%2F104228869.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fat-least-16-migrants-killed-29-injured-in-a-bus-crash-in-southern-mexico%2Famp_articleshow%2F104228869.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fat-least-16-migrants-killed-29-injured-in-a-bus-crash-in-southern-mexico%2Famp_articleshow%2F104228869.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Decadal%20Data%20Shows%20India%20Fails%20to%20Reduce%20Rate%20of%20Premature%20Births%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06180109%2Fcharles-eugene-6eEEsClXoNs-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Fhealth%2Findia-failed-reduce-premature-births-previous-decade%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20article%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0was%20originally%20published%20on%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Wire%20Science%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Ci%3Eour%20website%20dedicated%20to%20science%2C%20health%20and%20environment%20reportage%20and%20analysis.%20Follow%2C%20read%20and%20share.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%20has%20not%20shown%20any%20improvement%20in%20reducing%20preterm%20or%20premature%20births%20in%20the%20previous%20decade%2C%20reveals%20a%20new%20analysis%20published%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Lancet%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eon%20Friday%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20October%206.%20This%20is%20in%20contrast%20with%20the%20improvements%20that%20the%20country%20has%20made%20in%20other%20maternal%20and%20child%20mortality%20indicators%20over%20the%20same%20time%20period.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flancet%2Farticle%2FPIIS0140-6736(23)00878-4%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epaper%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20analysed%20preterm%20births%20in%202020%20across%20194%20countries%20and%20compared%20them%20with%20trends%20from%202010.%20It%20found%20that%20the%20preterm%20birth%20rate%20%E2%80%93%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0i.e.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20number%20of%20births%20that%20took%20place%20prematurely%20every%201000%20live%20births%20%E2%80%93%20was%2013.0%20in%202020%2C%20almost%20identical%20to%20the%20rate%20of%2013.1%20in%202010.%20A%20preterm%20birth%20is%20defined%20as%20a%20baby%20who%20is%20born%20before%20the%2037th%20week%20of%20gestation%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20the%20normal%20term%20of%2040%20weeks.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20contributed%2020%25%20of%20all%20preterm%20births%20(3%C2%B702%20million)%20%E2%80%93%20the%20highest%20in%20the%20world.%20It%20was%20followed%20by%20Pakistan%2C%20Nigeria%2C%20China%2C%20Ethiopia%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20the%20Democratic%20Republic%20of%20the%20Congo%2C%20and%20the%20US.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20these%20absolute%20numbers%20must%20be%20interpreted%20with%20few%20caveats%2C%20two%20being%20the%20reflection%20of%20large%20population%20sizes%20and%20the%20high%20number%20of%20total%20births%20happening%20in%20these%20countries.%20The%20authors%20of%20the%20paper%20add%20that%20these%20high%20numbers%20of%20preterm%20births%20were%20also%20reflective%20of%20%E2%80%9Cweaker%20health%20systems%20that%20are%20unable%20to%20deliver%20high-quality%20family%20planning%2C%20antenatal%20care%2C%20and%20childbirth%20services%20to%20all%20individuals%20who%20need%20them%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPreterm%20births%20have%20a%20higher%20chance%20of%20neonatal%20mortality%20(children%20dying%20within%20one%20month%20of%20birth).%20India%20has%20significantly%20reduced%20the%20neonatal%20mortality%20rate%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E24.9%20per%201000%20live%20births%20according%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.mohfw.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FNFHS-5_Phase-II_0.pdf%5C%22%3ENational%20Family%20Health%20Survey%20(NFHS)%3C%2Fa%3E-5%20data%2C%20down%20from%2029.5%20in%20the%20previous%20survey.%3Cspan%3E%20Its%20share%20of%20the%20global%20newborn%20mortality%20burden%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unicef.org%2Findia%2Fwhat-we-do%2Fnewborn-and-child-health%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecame%20down%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20one-third%20in%201990%20to%20below%20a%20quarter%20now.%20But%20the%20country%20still%20registers%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fnews-room%2Ffact-sheets%2Fdetail%2Flevels-and-trends-in-child-mortality-report-2021%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ehighest%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20number%20of%20neonatal%20deaths%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20across%20the%20world.%20While%20preterm%20births%20are%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enot%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20only%20reason%20for%20neonatal%20deaths%2C%20they%20remain%20one%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20causes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ET.%20Sundararaman%2C%20former%20head%20of%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Health%20and%20Family%20Welfare%E2%80%99s%20National%20Health%20Systems%20Resource%20Centre%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Etold%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20preterm%20births%20strain%20a%20healthcare%20system.%20A%20child%20born%20before%20the%20full%20term%20will%20require%20special%20care%2C%20said%20Sundararaman%2C%20who%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0was%20not%20associated%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Lance%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Et%20paper%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSome%20of%20these%20babies%20are%20born%20so%20small%20(underweight)%20that%20it%20is%20a%20real%20challenge%20to%20save%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDr%20Vipin%20Vashishtha%2C%20a%20Bijnor-based%20paediatrician%20also%20not%20associated%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Lancet%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20paper%2C%20agreed.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20%5Bpreterm%20babies%5D%20may%20require%20resuscitation%2C%20ventilation%20to%20prevent%20asphyxia%E2%80%A6%20these%20services%20may%20not%20be%20readily%20available%20at%20the%20periphery%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBesides%20these%20special%20services%2C%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20paediatrician%20is%20also%20of%20utmost%20importance.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%E2%80%98Rural%20Health%20Statistics%20(RHS)%202021-22%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Feight-charts-to-explain-the-state-of-rural-healthcare-in-india%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eshow%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20there%20are%20thousands%20of%20community%20health%20centres%20(CHCs)%20across%20India%20that%20don%E2%80%99t%20even%20have%20a%20single%20paediatrician%20stationed.%20Take%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20More%20than%20600%20CHCs%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20child%20specialist.%20As%20many%20as%204%2C474%20CHCs%20across%20India%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20paediatrician.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20neonate%2C%20who%20develops%20complications%2C%20may%20require%20treatment%20in%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnhm.gov.in%2Fimages%2Fpdf%2Fprogrammes%2Fchild-health%2Fannual-report%2FTwo_Year_Progress_of_SNCUs-A_Brief_Report_(2011-12_%26amp%3B_2012-13).pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESpecial%20Newborn%20Care%20Unit%20(SNCU)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20It%20is%20a%20separate%20unit%20in%20close%20proximity%20to%20the%20labour%20room%20with%2012%20or%20more%20beds%20that%20is%20meant%20to%20be%20managed%20by%20adequately%20trained%20doctors%2C%20staff%20nurses%20and%20support%20staff%20to%20provide%2024%C3%977%20services.%20It%20is%20usually%20established%20at%20district%20hospitals%20(DHs)%20or%20sub-divisional%20hospitals.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%2C%20the%20same%20RHS%202021-22%20says%20there%20is%20a%20shortage%20of%20more%20than%205%2C000%20doctors%20and%20about%2016%2C000%20paramedical%20staff%20members%20across%20district%20hospitals%20in%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20while%20there%20is%20a%20high%20burden%20of%20preterm%20births%20in%20the%20country%2C%20there%20is%20inadequate%20healthcare%20service%20delivery%20to%20prevent%20the%20death%20of%20neonates%20born%20prematurely%20and%20who%20may%20go%20on%20to%20develop%20complications.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENot%20all%20prematurely%20born%20kids%20face%20the%20risk%20of%20neonatal%20mortality.%20But%20many%20may%20experience%20a%20delay%20in%20brain%20development%2C%20cognitive%20impairment%20or%20cerebral%20palsy%2C%20Dr%20Vashishtha%20said.%20If%20proper%20facilities%20for%20neonatal%20care%20are%20available%2C%20many%20of%20these%20complications%20can%20be%20avoided.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBesides%2C%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation%20(WHO)%2C%20in%20its%20report%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fpublications%2Fi%2Fitem%2F9789240073890%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBorn%20Too%20Soon%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98%20released%20in%20May%202023%20reckoned%20premature%20births%20as%20one%20of%20the%20two%20underlying%20causes%20of%20low%20birth%20weight.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CLow-birth-weight%20newborns%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20become%20children%20who%20are%20stunted%20or%20wasted%2C%20and%20to%20experience%20developmental%20delays%2C%20and%20more%20likely%20to%20become%20undernourished%20adolescents%2C%20and%20then%20undernourished%20adults%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fin-2020-13-million-babies-were-born-too-early-india-is-among-top-five-nations-where-it-happened%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98In%202020%2C%2013%20Million%20Babies%20Were%20Born%20Too%20Early.%20India%20Is%20Among%20Top%20Five%20Nations%20Where%20It%20Happened%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20preterm%20births%20avoidable%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECan%20preterm%20births%20be%20avoided%3F%20The%20answer%20to%20this%20question%20lies%20in%20the%20circumstances%20leading%20to%20them.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Lancet%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20paper%20says%2C%20yes%2C%20they%20can%20be.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20underlying%20reasons%20that%20women%20deliver%20a%20child%20before%20the%20full%20term%20is%20the%20below-par%20care%20they%20receive%20during%20pregnancy%2C%20also%20known%20as%20antenatal%20care%20(ANC).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20proper%20antenatal%20care%20is%20provided%2C%20a%20preterm%20pregnancy%20may%20be%20projected%20beforehand%2C%20and%20plans%20can%20be%20made%20accordingly.%20Also%2C%20infections%20are%20one%20of%20the%20main%20causes%20of%20preterm%20births%20%E2%80%93%20which%20can%20be%20diagnosed%20and%20treated%20with%20proper%20ANC.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20authors%20of%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20Lancet%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Epaper%20say%20that%20an%20expectant%20mother%20must%20receive%20eight%20antenatal%20checkups%20at%20a%20healthcare%20facility.%20While%20Indian%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnhm.gov.in%2Fimages%2Fpdf%2Fprogrammes%2Fmaternal-health%2Fguidelines%2Fsba_guidelines_for_skilled_attendance_at_birth.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eguidelines%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20recommend%20a%20minimum%20of%20four%2C%20data%20shows%20that%20even%20that%20target%20is%20not%20met%20for%20a%20significant%20chunk%20of%20pregnant%20women.%20According%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.mohfw.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FNFHS-5_Phase-II_0.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENFHS-5%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20little%20more%20than%20half%20of%20pregnant%20women%20%E2%80%93%2058.1%25%20%E2%80%93%20received%20four%20ANC%20check-ups.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMoreover%2C%20these%20are%20merely%20the%20numbers.%20In%20other%20words%2C%2058.1%25%20of%20women%20went%20to%20a%20healthcare%20facility%20at%20least%20four%20times%20during%20pregnancy%20%E2%80%93%20but%20we%20do%20not%20know%20anything%20about%20the%20quality%20of%20ANC%20they%20received.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20clues%20about%20the%20quality%20of%20ANC%20can%20be%20gleaned%20from%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fobgyn.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1111%2F1471-0528.15825%5C%22%3Epaper%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3Cem%3EBJOG%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20journal%20of%20the%20Royal%20College%20of%20Obstetricians%20and%20Gynaecologists)%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EJuly%202019.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThree%20of%20the%20five%20authors%20of%20the%20paper%20%3C%2Fspan%3Ewere%20funded%20by%20the%20Indian%20Council%20of%20Medical%20Research%3Cspan%3E.%20They%20used%20the%20NFHS-4%20data%2C%20which%20said%2051%25%20of%20women%20received%20four%20ANC%20check-ups%2C%20to%20find%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eless%20than%20a%20quarter%20%E2%80%93%2023.5%25%20%E2%80%93%20of%20them%20got%20what%20they%20describe%20as%20%E2%80%9Cadequate%20ANC%E2%80%9D.%20As%20many%20as%2058.8%25%20received%20%E2%80%9Cinadequate%20ANC%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20used%20eight%20indicators%20to%20determine%20if%20ANC%20was%20adequate%2C%20such%20as%20weight%20measurement%2C%20urine%20testing%2C%20blood%20samples%20for%20investigating%20infections%20in%20expecting%20women%2C%20and%20consumption%20of%20iron%20and%20folic%20acid%20tablets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20authors%20also%20found%20a%20rich-poor%20and%20rural-urban%20divide.%20About%20two%20out%20of%20five%20women%20belonging%20to%20the%20richest%20wealth%20quintile%20received%20adequate%20ANC%2C%20but%20this%20was%207.9%25%20among%20the%20poorest%20women.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2F08152223%2Ffreestocks-ux53SGpRAHU-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2F08152223%2Ffreestocks-ux53SGpRAHU-unsplash.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2F08152223%2Ffreestocks-ux53SGpRAHU-unsplash-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2F08152223%2Ffreestocks-ux53SGpRAHU-unsplash-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-551007%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image%20of%20a%20pregnant%20woman.%20Photo%3A%20Unsplash%40freestocks%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20second%20important%20factor%2C%20according%20to%20Sundararaman%2C%20is%20what%20are%20called%20social%20determinants%20of%20health.%20The%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Born%20Too%20Soon%E2%80%99%20report%20also%20lays%20stress%20on%20factors%20like%20management%20of%20anaemia%20and%20proper%20diet.%20%E2%80%9CNutritional%20deficiencies%2C%20particularly%20iron%20deficiency%20anaemia%2C%20can%20lead%20to%20preterm%20delivery%20and%20low%20birth%20weight%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%2C%20NFHS-5%20(conducted%20between%202019-21)%20revealed%20more%20than%20half%2C%20i.e.%2C%2052.2%25%20of%20pregnant%20women%20aged%2015-49%20years%20were%20anaemic.%20The%20corresponding%20figure%20for%20NFHS-4%20(conducted%20between%202015-16)%20was%2050.4%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CMerely%20a%20woman%20paying%20three%20or%20four%20visits%20to%20a%20nearby%20health%20facility%20%5Bfor%20ANC%5D%20won%E2%80%99t%20serve%20much%20purpose%20unless%20these%20social%20determinants%20of%20health%20%E2%80%93%20nutrition%20and%20anaemia%20%E2%80%93%20are%20not%20addressed%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sundararaman%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20Dr%20Vashishtha%20agreed%20that%20these%20lacunae%20in%20addressing%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Epreventable%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20causes%20of%20preterm%20births%2C%20he%20also%20said%20a%20%E2%80%9Clarge%20number%20of%E2%80%9D%20such%20births%20are%20idiopathic%20%E2%80%93%20for%20which%20the%20cause%20could%20not%20be%20known.%20Although%20there%20is%20no%20nationwide%20study%20to%20say%20what%20percentage%20of%20preterm%20births%20are%20idiopathic%2C%20the%20paper%20published%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3ELancet%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0does%20not%20count%20it%20as%20one%20of%20the%20reasons.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ajog.org%2Faction%2FshowPdf%3Fpii%3DS0002-9378%252811%252990785-6%5C%22%3Ecommentary%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EAmerican%20Journal%20of%20Obstetrics%20and%20Gynecology%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%201993%20says%20idiopathic%20preterm%20births%20can%20also%20be%20avoided.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20suggest%20that%20an%20exhaustive%20evaluation%20plan%20can%20identify%20possible%20causes%20in%20the%20majority%20(96%25)%20of%20cases%20of%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eidiopathic%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Epreterm%20labour%20that%20result%20in%20preterm%20delivery%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20read.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMultiple%20pregnancies%2C%20especially%20during%20the%20teenage%20years%2C%20are%20one%20of%20the%20driving%20factors%20of%20preterm%20births.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGlobal%20scenario%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20eight%20countries%20with%20the%20highest%20rate%20of%20preterm%20births%20(number%20of%20preterm%20births%20per%201000%20live%20births)%20remained%20unchanged%20between%202010%20and%202020%20%E2%80%93%20although%20the%20order%20of%20some%20has%20interchanged.%20These%20are%20India%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20China%2C%20Ethiopia%2C%20the%20US%2C%20the%20Democratic%20Republic%20of%20Congo%20and%20Nigeria.%20From%20the%20global%20point%20of%20view%20also%2C%20the%20scenario%20didn%E2%80%99t%20improve%20in%202020%20as%20compared%20to%202010.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAlthough%20most%20of%20the%20high%20preterm%20birth%20rates%20occur%20in%20low-income%20and%20middle-income%20countries%20and%20areas%2C%20rates%20of%2010%25%20or%20higher%20%5Bpreterm%20births%5D%20were%20also%20observed%20in%20high-income%20countries%20such%20as%20Greece%20and%20the%20USA%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20paper%20reads.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20authors%20make%20a%20significant%20observation.%20The%20survival%20of%20neonates%20born%20as%20early%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E26%20weeks%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20gestation%20in%20resource-rich%20settings%20are%20%E2%80%9Cmore%20likely%20to%20survive%20than%20those%20born%20in%20contexts%20with%20poor%20access%20to%20care%20regardless%20of%20gestational%20age%E2%80%9D.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20while%20some%20rich%20countries%20may%20also%20have%20a%20high%20number%20of%20preterm%20births%2C%20the%20chances%20of%20those%20babies%20surviving%20are%20much%20better%20there%20as%20compared%20to%20the%20ones%20where%20the%20healthcare%20facilities%20are%20poor.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696649418000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06180109%2Fcharles-eugene-6eEEsClXoNs-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fin-previous-decade-india-could-not-reduce-rate-of-premature-births%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Lack%20of%20proper%20medical%20care%20during%20pregnancy%20and%20poor%20nutritional%20status%20of%20women%20are%20the%20leading%20causes%20of%20preterm%20births%2C%20which%20contribute%20to%20a%20large%20number%20of%20kids%20dying%20within%20a%20month%20of%20their%20births.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fin-previous-decade-india-could-not-reduce-rate-of-premature-births%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BMomentous...%26quot%3B%3A%20PM's%20Big%20Praise%20As%20India%20Hits%20100%20At%20Asian%20Games%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20today%20congratulated%20the%20Indian%20contingent%20at%20the%20Hangzhou%20Asian%20Games%20today%20after%20they%20officially%20breached%20the%20100-medal%20mark.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPM%20Modi%20termed%20India's%20performance%20at%20the%20Asian%20Games%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bmomentous%20achievement%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20that%20the%20people%20of%20India%20are%20%26quot%3Bthrilled%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20country's%20success.%20He%20also%20congratulated%20the%20athletes%20for%20their%20efforts%2C%20saying%20that%20their%20awe-inspiring%20performances%20have%20%26quot%3Bma