t.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fin-the-popes-homeland-more-argentines-are-seeking-spiritual-answers-beyond-the-church%2Famp_articleshow%2F104227591.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fin-the-popes-homeland-more-argentines-are-seeking-spiritual-answers-beyond-the-church%2Famp_articleshow%2F104227591.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Jawan%20outperforms%20Dono%20and%20Thank%20You%20For%20Coming%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696645883000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104227531%2Cimgsize-45958.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fbox-office%2Fjawans-fall-continues-makes-only-rs1-86-crore-on-friday%2Farticleshow%2F104227555.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F104227555.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EJawan%20continues%20its%20downward%20spiral%20but%20collects%20more%20than%20new%20releases%20like%20Dono%20and%20Thank%20You%20For%20Coming.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22From%20Temple%20to%20Mosque%3A%20Transformations%20in%20the%20Jali%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06150317%2FJali_Fig.-2_pp-42-43.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20development%20of%20Islamic%20styles%20of%20architecture%20in%20Gujarat%20from%20the%20fourteenth%20century%2C%20a%20new%20set%20of%20ideas%20transformed%20the%20relatively%20small-scale%20temple%20%3Cem%3Ejali%3C%2Fem%3E%20into%20a%20prominent%20feature%20in%20shrines%20and%20mosques.%20The%20symbolic%20importance%20of%20light%20in%20Islam%2C%20the%20need%20for%20discreet%20spaces%20in%20mosque%20enclosures%20(%3Cem%3Emaqsura%3C%2Fem%3Es)%20for%20women%20and%20elite%20visitors%2C%20as%20well%20as%20new%20aesthetic%20preferences%20for%20walls%20of%20lightness%20and%20pattern%20ushered%20in%20this%20change.%20The%20grid-like%20%3Cem%3Ejali%3C%2Fem%3E%20(so-called%20%3Cem%3Esakhandaka%3C%2Fem%3E)%20found%20on%20the%20outer%20wall%20of%20a%20temple%20was%20adapted%20and%20expanded%20in%20mosques%20and%20tombs%2C%20sometimes%20enclosing%20the%20entire%20building%2C%20and%20in%20particular%20the%20tomb%20chamber.%20This%20style%20of%20%3Cem%3Ejali%3C%2Fem%3E%20grid%20contains%20repeating%20squares%2C%20each%20one%20bearing%20an%20individual%20sacred%20symbol%20almost%20identical%20to%20those%20from%20Jain%20and%20Hindu%20temples.%20A%20few%20modest%20innovations%20were%20added%20to%20the%20received%20formula%2C%20most%20notably%20a%20series%20of%20openwork%20mihrab-arch%20shaped%20openings%20in%20the%20uppermost%20line.%20The%20%3Cem%3Ejali%3C%2Fem%3E%20thus%20evolved%20from%20a%20minor%20feature%20to%20a%20key%20characteristic%20of%20the%20building.%20Gujarati%20Sultanate%20architecture%20is%20replete%20with%20extraordinary%20%3Cem%3Ejali%3C%2Fem%3E%20screens%2C%20serving%20as%20both%20decoration%20and%20function.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20architectural%20remains%20at%20Bharuch%2C%20Khambhat%2C%20and%20Dholka%20have%20some%20of%20the%20earliest%20Islamic%20buildings%20of%20Gujarat%20and%20important%20transitions%20in%20style%20and%20function%20can%20be%20observed%2C%20including%20the%20transformation%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Ejali%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20the%20reuse%20of%20temple%20architectural%20elements.%20The%20mosque%20at%20Dholka%2C%20built%20in%201333%20by%20Hilal%20Khan%20Qazi%2C%20a%20general%20of%20the%20Tughlaqs%2C%20features%20expansive%20%3Cem%3Ejali%3C%2Fem%3E%20screens%20in%20the%20upper%20level%20as%20well%20as%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3Ezenana%3C%2Fem%3E%20(women%E2%80%99s%20quarter)%20area.%20This%20early%20patron%20took%20steps%20to%20elevate%20the%20%3Cem%3Ejali%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20a%20new%20status%20and%20function%2C%20developing%20an%20influential%20new%20formula.%20The%20temple%20whose%20elements%20are%20reused%20to%20build%20this%20mosque%20might%20have%20had%20some%20existing%20perforated%20screens%20that%20were%20added%20to.%20But%20even%20so%20we%20can%20see%20an%20adaptation%20of%20Islamic%20aesthetics%20in%20the%20introduction%20of%20arched%20openings%20in%20the%20top%20line%20of%20the%20upper%20screen.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06150451%2Fjali-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06150451%2Fjali-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06150451%2Fjali-1-300x188.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06150451%2Fjali-1-1024x640.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678639%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHilal%20Khan%20Qazi%20mosque%2C%20Dholka%2C%20Gujarat%2C%201333.%3Cbr%3EPhotos%3A%20Abhinav%20Goswami%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20without%20doubt%20the%20masterpiece%20of%20all%20Gujarati%20%3Cem%3Ejali%3C%2Fem%3Es%20are%20of%20a%20type%20that%20stand%20apart%20for%20their%20lyricism%20and%20virtuosity%E2%80%94the%20Tree%20of%20Life%20carved%20screens%20of%20the%20Sidi%20Sayyid%20Mosque%20in%20Ahmedabad.%20The%20building%20was%20previously%20attributed%20to%20the%20patronage%20of%20a%20slave%20of%20Ahmad%20Shah%20I%20(r.%201411%E2%80%931442)%20but%20is%20now%20attributed%20to%20an%20Abyssinian%20nobleman%20of%20the%20time%20of%20Sultan%20Muzaffar%20III%20(r.%201561%E2%80%931572).%20Within%20the%20mosque%20enclosure%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Eqibla%3C%2Fem%3E%20wall%20and%20side%20walls%20contain%20a%20series%20of%20almost%20semi-circular%20arches.%20The%20upper%20sections%20of%20the%20arches%20are%20fitted%20with%20exquisitely%20carved%20%3Cem%3Ejali%3C%2Fem%3Es%2C%20particularly%20the%20two%20that%20flank%20the%20central%20mihrab.%20This%20pair%20of%20%3Cem%3Ejali%3C%2Fem%3Es%20is%20each%20carved%20with%20the%20central%20motif%20of%20a%20tree%2C%20different%20from%20each%20other%20but%20unified%20in%20overall%20style.%20One%20contains%20a%20magnificent%20blossoming%20tree%20whose%20outwardly%20curving%20branches%20form%20gracious%20and%20pleasingly%20asymmetrical%20floral%20arabesques%2C%20standing%20before%20an%20almost%20hidden%20straight%20palm%20tree.%20The%20other%20%3Cem%3Ejali%3C%2Fem%3E%20contains%20a%20taller%20and%20slimmer%20central%20tree%20with%20sinuously%20interlocked%20branches%2C%20flanked%20by%20smaller%20waving%20date%20palms%20with%20chevron%20trunks%20and%20flowering%20trees%2C%20each%20with%20distinct%20types%20of%20blossoms%20(see%20pp.%206%E2%80%937).%20Seven%20other%20perforated%20screens%20on%20the%20back%20and%20side%20walls%20of%20the%20building%20are%20regally%20carved%20in%20the%20square-grid%20style.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06150628%2FJali_Fig.-26_pp-62-63.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06150628%2FJali_Fig.-26_pp-62-63.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06150628%2FJali_Fig.-26_pp-62-63-300x186.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06150628%2FJali_Fig.-26_pp-62-63-1024x633.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678640%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22742%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ETree%20of%20Life%20jali%2C%20Sidi%20Sayyid%20Mosque%2C%20Ahmedabad%2C%20Gujarat%2C%201572%E2%80%9373.%20Photo%3A%20Abhinav%20Goswami%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%98Tree%20of%20Life%E2%80%99%20imagery%20reflects%20the%20importance%20of%20the%20tree%20motif%20as%20an%20ancient%20symbol%20of%20protection%2C%20fertility%20and%20divinity%20in%20Indian%20art%20and%20architecture.%20Images%20of%20the%20wish-fulfilling%20tree%20(%3Cem%3Ekalpavriksha%3C%2Fem%3E)%20and%20auspicious%20vines%20(%3Cem%3Evallijatika%3C%2Fem%3E)%20and%20leaves%20(%3Cem%3Epatrajatika%3C%2Fem%3E)%20appear%20widely%20in%20architectural%20ornament.%20Flowering%20trees%20in%20mosque%20and%20tomb%20decoration%20evoke%20the%20Tree%20of%20Immortality%20(%3Cem%3Eshajarat%20al-khuld%3C%2Fem%3E)%20or%20the%20Blessed%20Tree%20in%20Paradise%20(%3Cem%3Etuba%3C%2Fem%3E)%20mentioned%20in%20the%20Qur%E2%80%99an%2C%20or%20other%20metaphorical%20and%20actual%20trees%20described%20in%20Islamic%20literary%20and%20poetic%20tradition.%20The%20Sidi%20Sayyid%20%3Cem%3Ejali%3C%2Fem%3Es%20therefore%20blend%20the%20ideals%20of%20Indian%20and%20Islamic%20beneficence%20through%20their%20multi-layered%20and%20richly%20inflected%20arboreal%20imagery%20and%20powerful%20aesthetic%20language.%20Such%20fecund%20motifs%20exist%20all%20over%20Gujarati%20architecture%2C%20including%20in%20the%20sensitively%20carved%20trees%20adorning%20the%20cenotaph%20of%20Umar%20bin%20Ahmad%20al%20Kazeruni%20in%20Khambhat%20(1333).%20Yet%20the%20perceptible%20leap%20into%20a%20softer%20naturalism%20and%20decorative%20grace%20also%20reflects%20the%20influence%20of%20new%20aesthetics%20developing%20at%20the%20distant%20Mughal%20court%20in%20Delhi%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20Gujarat%E2%80%99s%20annexation%20in%201573.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20impact%20of%20Gujarati%20styles%20of%20art%20and%20architecture%20has%20been%20felt%20all%20around%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20rim%20for%20centuries.%20The%20manufacture%20and%20export%20of%20carved%20marble%20tombstones%20from%20Khambhat%20to%20east%20Africa%20and%20southeast%20Asia%20in%20the%20late%20medieval%20period%20reveals%20a%20pattern%20of%20exchange%20that%20likely%20applied%20to%20other%20goods%20as%20well.%20Gujarati%20textiles%20dating%20to%20as%20early%20as%20the%20fourteenth%20century%20have%20been%20located%20in%20collections%20in%20Fustat%2C%20Egypt%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Indonesia.%20Among%20them%20is%20a%20type%20of%20painted%20and%20printed%20textile%20featuring%20a%20characteristically%20shaped%20three-petalled%20floral%20blossom%20on%20a%20curving%20stem%20(the%20so-called%20Big%20Leaf%20style).%20This%20distinctive%20motif%20makes%20a%20rare%20appearance%20in%20a%20%3Cem%3Ejali%3C%2Fem%3E%20window%20square%20in%20the%20mosque%20of%20Ahmad%20Shah%20at%20Ahmedabad%20(1414)%2C%20demonstrating%20the%20fluid%20exchange%20of%20styles%20and%20symbols%20across%20media%20and%20region.%20The%20movement%20of%20Gujarati%20craftsmen%20across%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20continued%20well%20into%20the%20nineteenth%20century%2C%20partly%20facilitated%20by%20the%20administration%20of%20the%20British%20Raj.%20Therefore%2C%20it%20is%20not%20surprising%20to%20find%20styles%20of%20Gujarati%20carving%20in%20the%20nineteenth-century%20architecture%2C%20particularly%20doors%20and%20arches%20of%20the%20houses%2C%20in%20Stone%20Town%20in%20Zanzibar.%20Among%20the%20many%20designs%20seen%20are%20doors%20surmounted%20with%20an%20arch%20containing%20a%20deeply%20wrought%20perforated%20floral%20%3Cem%3Ejali%3C%2Fem%3E%20design%2C%20recalling%20those%20of%20the%20wooden%20%3Cem%3Ehaveli%3C%2Fem%3Es%20and%20doorways%20of%20Ahmedabad%2C%20Khambhat%20and%20other%20cities%20of%20Gujarat.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06150826%2FJali_Fig.-32_p-68.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06150826%2FJali_Fig.-32_p-68.jpg%201000w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06150826%2FJali_Fig.-32_p-68-300x248.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678642%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22825%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EBig%20Leaf-style%20textile%20from%20Gujarat%20for%20the%20Indonesian%20market%2C%20late%2014th%2C%20early%2015th%20century.%20Photo%3A%20The%20Metropolitan%20Museum%20of%20Art%2C%20%E2%80%98Purchase%2C%20Friends%20of%20Asian%20Art%20Gifts%2C%202005%2C%202005.407%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20455px)%2085vw%2C%20455px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06151107%2FJali_Fig.-33_p-69.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22455%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06151107%2FJali_Fig.-33_p-69.jpg%20585w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06151107%2FJali_Fig.-33_p-69-176x300.jpg%20176w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678643%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22778%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EJali%20window%20with%20textile-like%20motifs%2C%20mosque%20of%20Ahmad%20Shah%2C%20Ahmedabad%2C%20Gujarat%2C%20c.%201414.%20Photo%3A%20Navina%20Haidar%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20463px)%2085vw%2C%20463px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06151200%2FJali_Fig.-34_p-69.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22463%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fupload