%2C%20Texas%20in%20November%202020%20with%20her%20now-8-year-old%20son.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20ex-husband%20left%20the%20marriage%20right%20before%20Covid%20started.%20I%20was%20in%20a%20bad%20spot.%20I%20had%20a%20toddler.%20I%20wasn't%20working%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESouthern%20California%20is%20a%20really%20bad%20place%20to%20be%20when%20you're%20unemployed%20and%20suddenly%20divorced%20because%20you%20need%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20to%20survive%20there.%20And%20money%20was%20something%20I%20did%20not%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20really%20depressed.%20Jobs%20were%20shutting%20down%20in%20Southern%20California%20at%20that%20time.%20Everything%20was%20closed.%20My%20son's%20pre-school%20and%20his%20daycare%20shut%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20no%20job%20and%20I%20couldn't%20get%20a%20job%20because%20of%20the%20lack%20of%20daycare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20homeless%20situation%20in%20Costa%20Mesa%20became%20a%20much%20bigger%20issue%20too.%20I%20had%20people%20defecating%20on%20my%20lawn.%20One%20time%20someone%20dumped%20a%20whole%20bunch%20of%20food%20on%20my%20son's%20head%20when%20we%20were%20walking%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-texas-move-with-baby-safer-affordable-lifestyle-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20never%20felt%20safe%20in%20my%20area%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20felt%20like%20a%20prisoner%20in%20my%20apartment.%20I%20remember%20telling%20my%20dad%2C%20I'm%20just%20done.%20I%20want%20to%20fast-forward%20to%20the%20end%20of%20my%20life.%20I%20can't%20live%20like%20this%20anymore.%20I%20don't%20know%20what%20the%20answer%20is%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20here.%20There%20has%20to%20be%20another%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%20I%20saw%20this%20video%20of%20Texas.%20It%20was%20drone%20footage%20of%20a%20beautiful%20area%20in%20the%20Hill%20Country.%20It%20looked%20so%20peaceful%20and%20green%20in%20this%20quaint%20little%20town.%20I%20said%2C%20that's%20where%20I%20want%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20whim%2C%20I%20did%20it.%20I%20didn't%20have%20money%20for%20a%20flight%20so%20I%20went%20on%20a%20train%20with%20my%20son.%20It%20took%2024%20hours%20to%20get%20to%20San%20Antonio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20like%20I%20stepped%20onto%20another%20planet.%20I%20was%20at%20the%20Riverwalk%20and%20there%20were%20people%20around.%20They%20weren't%20stuck%20in%20their%20houses.%20They%20were%20going%20to%20restaurants%20%E2%80%94%20in%20masks%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they%20were%20living%20their%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20came%20back%20from%20my%20trip%20and%20said%20to%20my%20ex-husband%2C%20I%20know%20this%20might%20sound%20crazy%2C%20but%20we%20have%20split%20custody%20and%20I%20want%20to%20move%20to%20Texas.%20You%20have%20to%20come%20too%20because%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20take%20your%20son%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20thinking%20he%20would%20say%20no.%20But%20he%20said%20he%20hated%20California%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rest%20was%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Side%20by%20side%20photos%20of%20Janelle%20Crossan%20and%20her%20son.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652097f26561dd877e73e597%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJanelle%20Crossan%20told%20Insider%20that%20she's%20fallen%20in%20love%20with%20Texas%20and%20would%20never%20move%20back%20to%20California.%20%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Janelle%20Crossan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20moved%20to%20New%20Braunfels%20in%20November%202020.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20Braunfels%20is%20one%20of%20the%20top%2010%20fastest-growing%20cities%20in%20the%20US.%20It's%20almost%20100%2C000%20people%20now.%20But%20it's%20still%20set%20up%20like%20an%20adorable%20small%20town.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20looks%20like%20a%20Hallmark%20movie.%20It's%20a%20cute%20little%20town%20with%20parades%20and%20festivals.%20We%20have%20a%20beautiful%20river%20that%20people%20come%20to%20to%20go%20tubing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20came%20here%20at%20first%2C%20I%20was%20thinking%20I%20might%20live%20in%20San%20Antonio.%20I%20thought%20maybe%20I'm%20more%20of%20a%20city%20person.%20But%20I%20just%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20the%20small-town%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20lot%20easier%20to%20get%20a%20job%20here.%20Once%20I%20had%20a%20job%20in%20Texas%2C%20I%20got%20a%20cheap%20little%20apartment%20with%20my%20son.%20In%20the%20last%20three%20years%2C%20I've%20moved%20up%20to%20a%20much%20higher-paying%20job.%20I%20don't%20make%20that%20much%20money%2C%20but%20I%20was%20thinking%20of%20moving%20out%20of%20my%20apartment%20into%20a%20nicer%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20started%20asking%20me%2C%20why%20don't%20you%20just%20buy%20a%20house%3F%20I%20would%20never%20have%20dreamed%20I%20could%20buy%20a%20house.%20That's%20for%20rich%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20people%20started%20telling%20me%20about%20all%20these%20programs%2C%20like%20the%20Texas%20first-time%20homebuyer%2C%20that%20you%20can%20qualify%20for.%20I%20started%20doing%20some%20research.%20I%20set%20up%20an%20appointment%20with%20a%20builder.%20They%20put%20me%20in%20contact%20with%20a%20loan%20mortgage%20officer%20who%20helped%20me%20qualify%20for%20a%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mortgage%20officer%20helped%20me%20over%20the%20course%20of%20a%20couple%20of%20months%20consolidate%20my%20debt%20and%20pay%20off%20my%20debt%2C%20making%20sure%20I%20had%20a%20good%20debt-to-income%20ratio%20so%20I%20would%20be%20approved.%20To%20make%20a%20long%20story%20short%2C%20I%20got%20a%20home%20with%20no%20down%20payment.%20I%20just%20pay%20the%20mortgage%20every%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20changed%20my%20life.%20I%20remember%20thinking%20in%20California%20that%20that%20was%20the%20end.%20I've%20already%20been%20married.%20It%20didn't%20work%20out.%20I'm%20never%20going%20to%20have%20a%20stable%20job.%20I'm%20never%20going%20to%20have%20enough%20money%20to%20support%20myself%20and%20my%20son.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20paid%20%241%2C750%20for%20rent%20in%20a%20crappy%20little%20apartment%20in%20California.%20Now%2C%20three%20years%20later%2C%20my%20whole%20payment%2C%20including%20mortgage%20and%20property%20taxes%20is%20%241%2C800%20a%20month%20for%20my%20three-bedroom%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20house%20changed%20everything.%20It's%20not%20just%20a%20home.%20This%20is%20my%20future.%20This%20is%20what%20I'm%20going%20to%20give%20my%20son%20when%20he's%20old%20and%20I%20pass%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Janelle%20Crossan%20was%20able%20to%20purchase%20a%20home%20in%20Texas%20after%20living%20in%20an%20apartment%20in%20California.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652096a86561dd877e73e52b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221142%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJanelle%20Crossan%20was%20able%20to%20purchase%20a%20home%20in%20Texas%20after%20living%20in%20an%20apartment%20in%20California.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Janelle%20Crossan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20son%20turned%20into%20an%20immediate%20Texan.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20son%20loves%20it%20in%20Texas.%20We%20moved%20here%20right%20when%20he%20turned%20five%20so%20most%20of%20his%20memories%20are%20now%20here.%20He%20loves%20being%20outdoors%20and%20going%20on%20camping%20trips%20and%20tubing%20in%20the%20river.%20He's%20taking%20archery.%20The%20school%20system%20here%20is%20much%20better%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20the%20South%20and%20its%20hospitality.%20The%20people%20are%20very%20friendly.%20You%20can%20talk%20to%20anyone%20on%20the%20street%20and%20probably%20trust%20them.%20I%20still%20find%20it%20a%20bit%20difficult%20to%20make%20friends.%20I'm%20not%20sure%20why%20that%20is.%20Maybe%20I%20really%20just%20am%20from%20another%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolitically%2C%20I'm%20a%20strong%20libertarian.