ictures-67029261.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Lawsuit%20alleges%20undisclosed%20relationship%20involving%20federal%20judge%20that%20could%20cloud%20Corizon%20bankruptcy%20deal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22533%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20interior%20of%20a%20Texas%20courthouse%2C%20with%20US%20and%20Texas%20flags%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6520852b9f7ca8b2bbdcadd5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20US%20Bankruptcy%20Court%20for%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas%2C%20in%20Houston%2C%20where%20Judge%20David%20Jones%20presides.%3Cp%3EUS%20District%20%26amp%3B%20Bankruptcy%20Court%2C%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3ECorizon%2C%20a%20leading%20private%20prison%20health%20provider%2C%20pulled%20a%20Texas%20Two-Step%2C%20putting%20assets%20in%20YesCare%20and%20debts%20in%20Tehum.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ETehum%20then%20filed%20for%20bankruptcy%2C%20potentially%20leaving%20hundreds%20of%20prisoners%20claiming%20malpractice%20with%20pennies%20on%20the%20dollar.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EA%20court%20document%20claims%20the%20judge%20mediating%20the%20settlement%20deal%20is%20in%20a%20romantic%20relationship%20with%20YesCare's%20attorney.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20complaint%20filed%20this%20week%20in%20federal%20court%20casts%20doubt%20over%20the%20neutrality%20of%20the%20judge%20who%20oversaw%20bankruptcy%20settlement%20talks%20involving%20Corizon%2C%20once%20the%20nation's%20largest%20prison%20health%20care%20provider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Jones%2C%20the%20chief%20bankruptcy%20judge%20for%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas%2C%20and%20Elizabeth%20Freeman%2C%20his%20former%20law%20clerk%20and%20a%20successful%20bankruptcy%20attorney%2C%20have%20secretly%20been%20in%20a%20romantic%20relationship%20for%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24018713-michael-van-deelen-complaint%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20complaint%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20obtained%20by%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Corizon%20began%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorizon-health-bankruptcy-yescare-texas-two-step-law-2023-8%5C%22%3Ea%20controversial%20maneuver%20known%20as%20a%20Texas%20Two-Step%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20splitting%20the%20company%20into%20two%20parts%2C%20one%20with%20most%20of%20its%20assets%2C%20known%20as%20YesCare%2C%20and%20one%20with%20most%20of%20its%20debts%2C%20known%20as%20Tehum%2C%20which%20then%20filed%20for%20bankruptcy.%20The%20Two%20Step%20was%20effectively%20designed%20to%20protect%20YesCare's%20assets%2C%20including%20public%20sector%20contracts%20worth%20more%20than%20%241%20billion.%20According%20to%20a%20legal%20filing%2C%20Tehum%20director%20Isaac%20Lefkowitz%20said%20the%20Two%20Step%20can%20be%20used%20to%20%26quot%3Bforce%20plaintiffs%20into%20accepting%20lower%20settlements.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFreeman%20represented%20YesCare%20Corp.%20in%20the%20settlement%20talks.%20And%20the%20talks%20were%20overseen%20by%20Jones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20350%20malpractice%20suits%20against%20Corizon%20and%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20unpaid%20invoices%20are%20now%20folded%20into%20that%20proposed%20deal%2C%20which%20awaits%20approval%20by%20the%20creditors.%20It%20offers%20prisoners%20who%20were%20injured%20or%20died%20under%20Corizon's%20care%20only%20%245%2C000%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20complaint%2C%20submitted%20on%20Wednesday%20in%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas%2C%20is%20currently%20not%20available%20for%20public%20access%20on%20the%20docket%2C%20Insider%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24018713-michael-van-deelen-complaint%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20obtained%20a%20copy%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Michael%20Van%20Deelen%2C%20who%20filed%20the%20suit%20pro%20se.%20It%20alleges%20that%20Jones%20retaliated%20against%20him%20for%20%26quot%3Bouting%26quot%3B%20the%20judge's%20allegedly%20inappropriate%20relationship%20in%20a%20previous%20legal%20filing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJones%20was%20appointed%20in%20May%20by%20US%20Bankruptcy%20Judge%20Christopher%20Lopez%20to%20act%20as%20a%20mediator%20in%20the%20Tehum%20case%2C%20to%20oversee%20talks%20between%20the%20company%20and%20its%20largest%20creditors.%20Freeman%20signed%20off%20on%20Jones'%20appointment%20as%20mediator%2C%20according%20to%20a%20stipulation%20and%20agreed%20order%20submitted%20in%20the%20bankruptcy%20docket.%20Neither%20Jones%20nor%20Freeman%20have%20disclosed%20their%20alleged%20relationship%2C%20according%20to%20Van%20Deelen's%20complaint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22887%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20excerpt%20from%20a%20civil%20complaint%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65208b646561dd877e73df09%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22443%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20civil%20complaint%20alleges%20that%20federal%20bankruptcy%20judge%20David%20Jones%2C%20who%20mediated%20the%20Tehum%20bankruptcy%2C%20is%20in%20a%20romantic%20relationship%20with%20Elizabeth%20Freeman%2C%20who%20represented%20YesCare%20in%20the%20bankruptcy.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Michael%20Van%20Deelen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3EFrank%20Ozment%2C%20who%20represents%20an%20Alabama%20prisoner%2C%20Tracy%20Grissom%2C%20who%20said%20she%20was%20subjected%20to%20negligent%20Corizon%20care%2C%20called%20the%20claims%20%26quot%3Bvery%20disturbing%26quot%3B%20if%20true.%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20important%20that%20the%20mediator%20be%20neutral%2C%26quot%3B%20Ozment%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20allegations%20suggest%20that%20the%20mediator%20was%20not%20neutral%2C%20then%20that%20could%20potentially%20bear%20a%20lot%20of%20weight%20on%20whether%20the%20plan%20is%20reasonable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJones%20has%20denied%20any%20romantic%20relationship%20with%20Freeman%2C%20according%20to%20the%20complaint.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJones%2C%20Freeman%2C%20and%20YesCare%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20queries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20million-dollar%20home%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EVan%20Deelen's%20case%20dates%20back%20to%20June%202020%2C%20when%20he%20filed%20a%20shareholder%20suit%20in%20Texas%20state%20court%20against%20employees%20of%20engineering%20company%20McDermott%20International%2C%20alleging%20fraud%20and%20a%20breach%20of%20duty.%20Six%20months%20earlier%2C%20McDermott%20had%20declared%20bankruptcy.%20Van%20Deelen%20says%20he%20and%20his%20wife%20lost%20their%20entire%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcDermott%20was%20represented%20in%20the%20case%20by%20law%20firm%20Jackson%20Walker%2C%20one%20of%20the%20country's%20top%20bankruptcy%20firms.%20Freeman%20clerked%20for%20Jones%20for%20six%20years%2C%20and%20she%20went%20on%20to%20become%20a%20partner%20at%20Jackson%20Walker%2C%20where%20she%20was%20one%20of%20the%20attorneys%20assigned%20to%20the%20McDermott%20bankruptcy.%20Van%20Deelen's%20case%20was%20ultimately%20%26quot%3Bremoved%26quot%3B%20to%20Jones'%20bankruptcy%20court%2C%20according%20to%20Van%20Deelen's%20complaint.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFreeman%20now%20runs%20a%20Houston-based%20law%20office%2C%20The%20Law%20Office%20of%20Liz%20Freeman%2C%20that%20specializes%20in%20bankruptcy%20litigation%20and%20reorganization.%20Van%20Deelen%20claims%20Freeman%20left%20her%20prestigious%20job%20at%20Jackson%20Walker%20because%20%26quot%3Bthe%20relationship%20between%20her%20and%20Defendant%20Jones%20was%20made%20generally%20known.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20document%20alleges%20that%2C%20while%20working%20the%20McDermott%20case%2C%20Freeman%20was%20Jones'%20%26quot%3Blive-in%20girlfriend%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20home%20worth%20more%20than%20a%20million%20dollars.%20Exhibits%20attached%20to%20the%20complaint%20show%20that%20Jones%20and%20Freeman%20have%20since%20June%202017%20been%20listed%20as%20co-owners%20of%20a%20four-bed%2C%20two-bath%2C%203%2C800%20square%20foot%20home%20on%20a%20leafy%20street%20in%20Houston%20that%20was%20assessed%20at%20%241.07%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20two%20people%2C%20%26quot%3Bprobably%20Freeman's%20parents%26quot%3B%20moved%20into%20a%20%241.5%20million%20home%20that%20Jones%20owns%20in%20Coldspring%2C%20an%20hour%20outside%20of%20Houston%2C%20according%20to%20another%20exhibit.%20The%20complaint%20alleges%20that%20Freeman%20had%20been%20living%20in%20that%20property%20since%202007%2C%20and%20that%20Jones%20purchased%20it%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVan%20Deelen%20said%20in%20the%20suit%20that%20he%20learned%20of%20the%20relationship%20after%20receiving%20an%20anonymous%20letter%20in%20March%202021%2C%20also%20attached%20as%20an%20exhibit.%20It%20describes%20alleged%20corruption%20that%20involved%20Jones%2C%20Jackson%20Walker%2C%20and%20Freeman%20%26quot%3Bin%20a%20scheme%20in%20which%20corporate%20bankruptcy%20filers%20would%20hire%20Jackson%20Walker%20to%20represent%20them%20and%20then%20get%20favorable%20treatment%20from%20Defendant%20Jones%20because%20of%20his%20amorous%20relationship%20with%20Freeman.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMatt%20Cavenaugh%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20Jackson%20Walker%2C%20didn't%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20complaint%2C%20the%20letter%20detailed%20the%20%26quot%3Bcorruption%20involving%20Judge%20David%20R.%20Jones%26quot%3B%20and%20his%20romantic%20relationship%20with%20Freeman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstead%20of%20personally%20avoiding%20the%20McDermott%20bankruptcy%20case%20because%20of%20his%20relationship%20with%20Jackson%20Walker%20attorney%20Freeman%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20complaint%20says%2C%20Jones%20%26quot%3Bassigned%20the%20case%20to%20himself.%26quot%3B%20He%20didn't%20disclose%20that%20he%20had%20a%20personal%20relationship%20with%20Freeman%2C%20according%20to%20the%20complaint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVan%20Deelen%20submitted%20the%20letter%20in%20a%20motion%20seeking%20to%20get%20Jones%20removed%20from%20his%20case.%20Judge%20Marvin%20Isgur%2C%20another%20bankruptcy%20judge%20in%20the%20court%2C%20later%20denied%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVan%20Deelen%20said%20that%20when%20he%20filed%20the%20complaint%2C%20he%20also%20hand%20delivered%20it%20to%20Jones%20in%20the%20Houston%20courthouse.%20After%20making%20his%20way%20through%20the%20maze%20of%20offices%2C%20Van%20Deelen%20said%20he%20turned%20a%20corner%20to%20find%20Jones%20eating%20a%20sandwich.%20When%20the%20judge%20saw%20who%20it%20was%2C%20%26quot%3Bhe%20turned%20white%2C%26quot%3B%20Van%20Deelen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20Jones%20accepted%20the%20envelope%20without%20saying%20a%20word.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprison-health-provider-corizon-bankruptcy-clouded-by-judge-romantic-relationship-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696634514000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6520863e6561dd877e73dd05%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprison-health-provider-corizon-bankruptcy-clouded-by-judge-romantic-relationship-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20attorney%20for%20Corizon%20successor%20company%20YesCare%20is%20in%20a%20romantic%20relationship%20with%20federal%20judge%20David%20Jones%2C%20a%20suit%20claims.%20Jones%20was%20mediator%20on%20the%20prison%20health%20care%20provider's%20bankruptcy%20deal%2C%20which%20could%20benefit%20YesCare.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22dcampbell%40insider.com%20(Dakin%20Campbell%2CNicole%20Einbinder)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A37%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprison-health-provider-corizon-bankruptcy-clouded-by-judge-romantic-relationship-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%2