e%20more%20slowly%20if%20you%20travel%20at%20nearly%20the%20speed%20of%20light%3F%3Cp%3EBettmann%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELet's%20say%20you%20have%20a%20twin%20who%20was%20born%20at%20almost%20the%20exact%20same%20time%20as%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20almost%20immediately%2C%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feinstein-reveals-manipulate-time-2016-3%5C%22%3Etwin%20boards%20a%20spaceship%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20launches%20into%20space%20to%20travel%20through%20the%20universe%20at%20nearly%20the%20speed%20of%20light.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%2C%20according%20to%20Einstein's%20special%20theory%20of%20relativity%2C%20time%20moves%20slower%20the%20closer%20you%20reach%20the%20speed%20of%20light%2C%20your%20twin%20in%20the%20spaceship%20would%20age%20more%20slowly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20spaceship%20landed%20back%20on%20Earth%2C%20you%20would%20be%20celebrating%20your%2065th%20birthday%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.omnicalculator.com%2Fphysics%2Ftime-dilation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyour%20twin%3C%2Fa%3E%20hadn't%20even%20turned%2010%20yet%2C%20based%20on%20an%20estimation%20from%20Omni%20Calculator.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20your%20elevator%20accelerating%20or%20floating%20in%20space%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22981%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Albert%20Einstein%20sits%20in%20a%20chair%20behind%20a%20wooden%20table%20on%20his%20porch%20at%20home%20in%20Princeton%2C%20New%20Jersey.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652048e79f7ca8b2bbdc34c0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22735%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhy%20do%20forces%20like%20gravity%20and%20acceleration%20feel%20the%20same%3F%3Cp%3EErnst%20Haas%20%2F%20Contributor%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EImagine%20you%20are%20in%20a%20windowless%20elevator%2C%20unable%20to%20see%20what's%20happening%20outside.%20Without%20visual%20cues%2C%20you%20don't%20know%20if%20you're%20in%20a%20stationary%20elevator%20on%20Earth%20or%20in%20space%20being%20hauled%20upwards.%20Gravity's%20tug%20and%20upward%20acceleration%20in%20zero%20gravity%20both%20pull%20you%20to%20the%20floor.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20physics%20of%20both%20events%20is%20the%20same%2C%20Einstein%20decided%2C%20based%20on%20the%20%26quot%3Bprinciple%20of%20equivalence.%26quot%3B%20Similarly%2C%20if%20your%20elevator%20were%20to%20plummet%20far%20and%20fast%2C%20you%20would%20float%20as%20though%20you%20were%20in%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20consider%20Einstein's%20previous%20assertion%20that%20time%20and%20space%20are%20relative.%20If%20motion%20can%20affect%20time%20and%20space%20(like%20with%20the%20train%20experiment)%20and%20gravity%20and%20acceleration%20behave%20the%20same%2C%20that%20means%20gravity%20can%20actually%20affect%20time%20and%20space.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20put%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fphysics.aps.org%2Farticles%2Fv4%2F43%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebowling%20ball%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20a%20trampoline%2C%20it%20will%20depress%20the%20fabric.%20Place%20marbles%20close%20by%2C%20and%20they%20will%20roll%20toward%20the%20ball.%20Objects%20with%20huge%20mass%20can%20affect%20space-time%20in%20a%20similar%20way.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ability%20of%20gravity%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblack-hole-warps-space-astronomers-see-light-behind-it-2021-8%5C%22%3Ewarp%20space-time%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cfa.harvard.edu%2Fresearch%2Fscience-field%2Feinsteins-theory-gravitation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekey%20part%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Einstein's%20general%20theory%20of%20relativity%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.space.com%2F17661-theory-general-relativity.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20decade%20after%20the%20special%20theory%20and%20expanded%20upon%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20particles%20communicate%20faster%20than%20the%20speed%20of%20light%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Einstein%20sticks%20his%20tongue%20out%20standing%20next%20to%20another%20man%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64cc246e0f3dff001956c9da%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhat%20is%20spooky%20action%20at%20a%20distance%3F%3Cp%3EBettmann%20%2F%20Contributor%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEinstein%20wasn't%20the%20biggest%20cheerleader%20for%20quantum%20theory.%20In%20fact%2C%20he%20argued%20back%20and%20forth%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmanhattan-project-scientists-who-won-nobel-prizes-2023-7%5C%22%3Ephysicist%20Niels%20Bohr%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20certain%20occurrences%20that%20he%20believed%20violated%20fundamental%20laws%20of%20physics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Einstein's%20thought%20experiments%20had%20to%20do%20with%20quantum%20entanglement%2C%20which%20he%20called%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquantum-entanglement-einstein-first-picture-2019-7%5C%22%3Espooky%20action%20at%20a%20distance%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImagine%20you%20have%20a%20two-sided%20coin%20that%20you%20can%20easily%20split%20in%20half.%20You%20flip%20the%20coin.%20Without%20looking%20at%20the%20outcome%2C%20you%20hand%20one%20side%20to%20your%20friend%20and%20keep%20the%20other%20side%20for%20yourself.%20Then%20your%20friend%20gets%20on%20a%20rocket%20ship%20and%20travels%20across%20the%20universe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20look%20at%20your%20coin%2C%20you%20see%20you're%20holding%20the%20heads%20side%20of%20the%20coin.%20Instantly%20you%20know%20that%20your%20friend%2C%20who%20is%20billions%20of%20light%20years%20away%2C%20has%20the%20tails%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20of%20Albert%20Einstein%20taken%20on%20December%2030%2C%201932.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F641ca3d9d67fe70018a3776a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22791%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMany%20scientists%20have%20spent%20decades%20researching%20Einstein's%20thought%20experiments.%3Cp%3EBettmann%20%2F%20Contributor%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEinstein's%20version%20of%20this%20thought%20experiment%20is%20more%20complicated%20than%20coins%20and%20involves%20entangled%20particles%20that%20share%20a%20wave%20function.%20Both%20particles%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20be%20in%20two%20possible%20states%2C%20spin%20up%20and%20spin%20down.%20Measuring%20one%20gives%20you%20information%20about%20the%20other%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20far%20apart%20they%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20bit%20like%20if%20your%20half%20of%20the%20coin%20was%20neither%20heads%20nor%20tails%20until%20you%20looked%20at%20it.%20Since%20the%20coin%20wasn't%20double-sided%2C%20you%20know%20your%20friend%20has%20tails%20when%20you%20have%20heads.%20But%20Einstein%20thought%20particles%20behaved%20more%20like%20real%20coins.%20They%20had%20some%20inherent%20property%20that%20made%20them%20%26quot%3Bspin%20up%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bspin%20down%26quot%3B%20all%20along.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20scientists%20have%20proven%20him%20wrong%20in%20the%20decades%20since.%20In%202022%2C%20three%20physicists%20won%20the%20Nobel%20Prize%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nobelprize.org%2Fprizes%2Fphysics%2F2022%2Fsummary%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efor%20demonstrating%3C%2Fa%3E%20spooky%20action%20at%20a%20distance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falbert-einstein-thought-experiments-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696618571000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6520473c6561dd877e735b0c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falbert-einstein-thought-experiments-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22One%20of%20Einstein's%20most%20defining%20qualities%20was%20his%20remarkable%20ability%20to%20conceptualize%20complex%20scientific%20ideas%20by%20imagining%20real-life%20scenarios.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Ali%20Sundermier%2CJenny%20McGrath)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A85%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falbert-einstein-thought-experiments-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ukraine%20is%20using%20%24100%2C000%20octocopter%20drones%20to%20destroy%20Russian%20tanks%20and%20artillery%20worth%20millions%2C%20even%20in%20the%20dead%20of%20night%2C%20operator%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Ukrainian%20drone%20operator%20from%20the%2024th%20Separate%20Mechanized%20Brigade%20tests%20new%20military%20equipment%20including%20FPV%20drones%20on%20the%20training%20area%20amid%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20in%20Donetsk%20Oblast%2C%20Ukraine%20on%20August%2003%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64da03af1f51cc001968b541%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20drone%20operator%20from%20the%2024th%20Separate%20Mechanized%20Brigade%20tests%20new%20military%20equipment%20including%20FPV%20drones%20on%20the%20training%20area%20amid%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20in%20Donetsk%20Oblast%2C%20Ukraine%20on%20August%2003%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EWojciech%20Grzedzinski%2FAnadolu%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EUkraine%20has%20been%20using%20homemade%20%24100%2C000%20octocopter%20drones%20to%20destroy%20Russian%20tanks%20on%20the%20battlefield%2C%20an%20operator%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20R18%20octocopters%20destroyed%2010%20Russian%20tanks%20in%20recent%20months%2C%20a%20drone%20pilot%20told%20CBS%20News.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EIn%20the%20last%20month%2C%20a%20Ukrainian%20military%20unit%20%26quot%3Bdestroyed%20%2440%20million%20worth%20of%20Russian%20hardware%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20commander%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20cheap%2C%20throwaway%20drones%20flying%20on%20the%20front%20lines%2C%20but%20some%20others%20come%20with%20higher%20price%20tags.%20One%20homemade%20octocopter%20runs%20for%20%24100%2C000%2C%20but%20this%20weapon%20appears%20to%20be%20proving%20its%20worth%2C%20taking%20out%20far%20more%20expensive%20Russian%20tanks%20and%20artillery%20pieces%2C%20even%20in%20the%20dead%20of%20night%2C%20an%20operator%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-the-elite-ukrainian-drone-unit-volunteer-it-experts-2022-4%5C%22%3EUkrainian-made%20R18%20octocopters%3C%2Fa%3E%20equipped%20with%20thermal%20imaging%20cameras%20and%20capable%20of%20carrying%20ordnance%20that%20can%20be%20dropped%20on%20enemy%20assets%20below%20have%20been%20wreaking%20havoc%20on%20the%20battlefield%20amid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fputin-orders-russia-troops-to-ukraine-major-escalation-2022-2%5C%22%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin's%20grinding%20war%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20Eastern%20European%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20drone%20operator%20with%20Ukraine's%2024th%20Separate%20Mechanized%20Brigade%2C%20who%20goes%20by%20the%20callsign%20Sunset%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fnews%2Fukraine-drone-unit-tells-cbs-40-million-dollars-russia-military-hardware-destroyed%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20