oping%20for%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Investors%20have%20been%20looking%20for%20the%20economy%20soften%2C%20which%20would%20likely%20influence%20the%20Fed%20to%20pull%20back%20on%20rate%20hikes.%20Officials%20raised%20rates%20525%20basis-points%20over%20the%20last%20year%20to%20lower%20inflation%20and%20cool%20economic%20growth%2C%20a%20move%20that%20has%20weighed%20heavily%20on%20stocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarkets%20see%20a%2029%25%20chance%20Fed%20officials%20hikes%20rates%20another%2025%20basis-points%20in%20November%2C%20up%20from%2020%25%20on%20Thursday%2C%20according%20to%20the%20CME%20FedWatch%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigher%20rates%20risk%20sparking%20a%20recession%2C%20especially%20considering%20interest%20rates%20are%20already%20higher%20than%20Fed%20officials%20think%2C%20Blitz%20said.%20Using%20the%20Taylor%20Index%20%E2%80%93%20an%20economic%20formula%20that%20calculates%20interest%20rates%20based%20on%20target%20inflation%2C%20the%20neutral%20rate%20of%20the%20economy%2C%20and%20other%20factors%20%E2%80%94%20Blitz%20estimated%20that%20interest%20rates%20in%20the%20economy%20could%20actually%20be%20around%205.75%25-6.75%25%2C%20above%20the%20official%20target%20range%20of%205.25%25-5.5%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIs%20the%20Fed%20convinced%20on%20this%20point%3F%20Probably%20not%2C%20so%20they%20will%20do%20what%20they%20always%20do%2C%20hike%20until%20something%20breaks%20%E2%80%93%20and%20rates%20are%20finally%20at%20the%20point%20where%20something%20can%20be%20broken%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarkets%20have%20panicked%20in%20recent%20weeks%20as%20investors%20try%20to%20adjust%20to%20a%20higher-for-longer%20interest%20rate%20environment.%20Yields%20on%20the%2010-year%20US%20Treasury%20just%20rose%20to%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Ffinancial-crisis-stock-market-crash-bonds-10-year-treasury-jpmorgan-2023-10%5C%22%3Ehighest%20level%20since%202007%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20briefly%20touching%204.8%2