2%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fenergy-exchange-iex-to-acquire-10-stake-in-enviro-enablers-india-123100601060_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fenergy-exchange-iex-to-acquire-10-stake-in-enviro-enablers-india-123100601060_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22No%20Immunity%20for%20Any%20Conspiracy%20Behind%20Ramesh%20Bidhuri%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Hate%20Speech%E2%80%99%20in%20Parliament%2C%20SC%20Told%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2F20172512%2F2022_5img20_May_2022_PTI05_20_2022_000129B-min.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Cspan%3EThe%20recent%20episode%20of%20a%20BJP%20member%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20Ramesh%20Bidhuri%2C%20using%20slurs%20against%20another%20member%2C%20Danish%20Ali%2C%20during%20a%20debate%20in%20the%20House%20came%20under%20scrutiny%20before%20the%20seven-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Thursday%20(October%205).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20question%20under%20consideration%20was%20whether%20Bidhuri%E2%80%99s%20conduct%20%E2%80%93%20which%20clearly%20would%20have%20constituted%20hate%20speech%20outside%20the%20House%20%E2%80%93%20could%20come%20under%20the%20cloak%20of%20parliamentary%20immunity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERaju%20Ramachandran%2C%20the%20senior%20counsel%20who%20argued%20before%20the%20bench%2C%20agreed%20that%20however%20despicable%20Bidhuri%E2%80%99s%20speech%20may%20have%20been%2C%20it%20enjoys%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20for%20criminality%20because%20he%20made%20it%20in%20the%20course%20of%20proceedings%20in%20parliament.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20Ramachandran%20added%20a%20caveat%2C%20saying%20that%20if%20there%20is%20evidence%20of%20a%20conspiracy%20before%20the%20debate%20to%20make%20the%20hate%20speech%2C%20then%20that%20conspiracy%20would%20not%20enjoy%20immunity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scobserver.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2FPV_Narsimha_Majority.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EP.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%20vs%20State%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%20five-judge%20bench%20in%201998%20held%20in%20a%203%3A2%20majority%20that%20legislators%20are%20immune%20to%20criminal%20prosecution%20for%20any%20speech%20or%20vote%20in%20the%20House%2C%20by%20virtue%20of%20the%20privilege%20conferred%20by%20Articles%20105(2)%20and%20194(2)%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20majority%20judges%2C%20led%20by%20Justice%20S.P.%20Bharucha%2C%20had%20held%20that%20the%20privilege%20could%20only%20be%20claimed%20if%20the%20legislator%2C%20who%20receives%20a%20bribe%20promising%20to%20vote%20or%20speak%20in%20the%20House%20to%20satisfy%20the%20bribe-giver%2C%20performs%20that%20promise.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20two%20dissenting%20judges%2C%20Justices%20S.C.%20Agarwal%20and%20A.S.%20Anand%2C%20however%2C%20took%20the%20view%20that%20the%20immunity%20granted%20under%20these%20two%20Articles%20would%20not%20extend%20to%20cases%20where%20bribery%20for%20making%20a%20speech%20or%20voting%20in%20a%20particular%20manner%20in%20the%20House%20is%20alleged.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Framesh-bidhuris-controversial-appointment-shows-hate-is-bjps-political-currency%5C%22%3ERamesh%20Bidhuri%E2%80%99s%20Controversial%20Appointment%20Shows%20Hate%20is%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Political%20Currency%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20seven-judge%20bench%20concluded%20its%20two-day%20hearing%20on%20the%20correctness%20of%20the%20majority%20view%20in%20this%20case%20on%20Thursday%2C%20October%205%2C%20and%20reserved%20its%20judgment.%20The%20bench%20comprised%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20and%20Justices%20A.S.%20Bopanna%2C%20M.M.%20Sundresh%2C%20P.S.%20Narasimha%2C%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%2C%20Sanjay%20Kumar%20and%20Manoj%20Misra.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20correctness%20of%20the%20decision%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EP.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20was%20referred%20for%20reconsideration%20by%20a%20seven-judge%20bench%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2014%2F10177%2F10177_2014_1_701_47406_Order_05-Oct-2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESita%20Soren%20v%20Union%20of%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESoren%2C%20who%20belongs%20to%20the%20Jharkhand%20Mukti%20Morcha%2C%20was%20accused%20of%20accepting%20a%20bribe%20to%20vote%20for%20an%20independent%20candidate%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20elections.%20She%20claimed%20immunity%20under%20Article%20194(2)%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20as%20per%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20majority%20verdict%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EP.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESoren%20failed%20to%20perform%20the%20promise%20made%20to%20the%20bribe-giver%20and%20voted%20for%20her%20party%E2%80%99s%20candidate%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20thereby%20not%20completing%20the%20offence%20of%20criminality.%20As%20the%20Jharkhand%20high%20court%20dismissed%20her%20plea%2C%20she%20filed%20her%20appeal%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20high%20court%20dismissed%20her%20plea%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20Soren%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20act%20of%20receiving%20the%20bribe%20had%20no%20nexus%20with%20the%20act%20of%20casting%20her%20vote%20in%20the%20assembly%2C%20as%20she%20did%20not%20vote%20for%20the%20bribe-giver.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EP.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20majority%20judges%20had%20held%20that%20if%20one%20casts%20a%20vote%20pursuant%20to%20the%20alleged%20conspiracy%20and%20agreement%2C%20then%20the%20latter%20can%20be%20said%20to%20have%20had%20a%20nexus%20with%20the%20vote.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EP.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20case%2C%20one%20of%20the%20accused%2C%20Ajit%20Singh%2C%20who%20was%20party%20to%20the%20conspiracy%20to%20receive%20a%20bribe%20to%20vote%20against%20the%20no-confidence%20motion%20against%20the%20then-Rao%20government%2C%20did%20not%20cast%20his%20vote%20and%20therefore%20was%20found%20ineligible%20for%20immunity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20majority%20judges%20in%20that%20case%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ereasoned%20that%20our%20sense%20of%20indignation%20(over%20bribery)%20should%20not%20lead%20us%20to%20construe%20the%20constitution%20as%20narrowing%20or%20impairing%20the%20guarantee%20to%20effective%20parliamentary%20participation%20and%20debate.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Frajya-sabha-gujarat-congress-mlas-election%5C%22%3ERS%20Polls%3A%20Gujarat%20Congress%20MLAs%20Who%20Quit%20Can%20Still%20Be%20Prosecuted%20if%20Bribery%20is%20Alleged%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20dissenting%20judges%2C%20however%2C%20recognised%20that%20while%20the%20object%20and%20purpose%20of%20Article%20105(2)%20of%20the%20constitution%20is%20to%20enable%20members%20of%20parliament%20to%20speak%20freely%20or%20to%20cast%20their%20votes%20without%20fear%20of%20consequences%2C%20an%20interpretation%20that%20places%20members%20of%20parliament%20above%20the%20law%20would%20be%20repugnant%20to%20the%20healthy%20functioning%20of%20parliamentary%20democracy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20dissenting%20judges%2C%20immunity%20would%20not%20extend%20to%20anything%20that%20occurred%20before%20a%20speech%20or%20a%20vote.%20This%2C%20they%20concluded%2C%20would%20be%20the%20result%20if%20one%20were%20to%20interpret%20the%20words%20%E2%80%9Cin%20respect%20of%E2%80%9D%20in%20Article%20105(2)%20as%20%E2%80%9Carising%20out%20of%E2%80%9D%2C%20so%20that%20the%C2%A0Article%20refers%20specifically%20to%20the%20consequences%20of%20a%20speech%20or%20vote%20given%20in%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EArticle%20105(2)%20says%20that%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ENo%20member%20of%20Parliament%20shall%20be%20liable%20to%20any%20proceedings%20in%20any%20court%20%3Cstrong%3Ein%20respect%20of%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20anything%20said%20or%20any%20vote%20given%20by%20him%20in%20Parliament%20or%20any%20committee%20thereof%2C%20and%20no%20person%20shall%20be%20so%20liable%20in%20respect%20of%20the%20publication%20by%20or%20under%20the%20authority%20of%20either%20House%20of%20Parliament%20of%20any%20report%2C%20paper%2C%20votes%20or%20proceedings.%20%5BEmphasis%20added%5D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThey%20also%20said%20this%20interpretation%20would%20prevent%20an%20anomaly%20%E2%80%93%20the%20majority%20judges%E2%80%99%20broad%20interpretation%20of%20%E2%80%9Cin%20respect%20of%E2%80%9D%20grants%20immunity%20to%20votes%20or%20speeches%20given%20due%20to%20bribery%2C%20but%20not%20to%20silence%20or%20abstention%20from%20voting%20as%20a%20result%20of%20bribery%20(as%20the%20wording%20in%20the%20Article%20does%20not%20mention%20abstention).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Carising%20out%20of%E2%80%9D%20interpretation%20grants%20immunity%20in%20neither%20situation%20(voting%20or%20abstaining%20after%20accepting%20a%20bribe)%2C%20as%20the%20act%20of%20accepting%20a%20bribe%20happens%20before%20any%20speech%20or%20vote%20in%20parliament%2C%20and%20not%20as%20a%20consequence%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20dissenting%20judges%20held%20that%20the%20offence%20of%20bribery%20is%20complete%20against%20the%20receiver%20of%20a%20bribe%2C%20if%20they%20take%20or%20agree%20to%20take%20money%20for%20a%20promise%20to%20act%20in%20a%20certain%20way.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20offence%20would%20be%20complete%20with%20the%20acceptance%20of%20the%20money%20or%20on%20the%20agreement%20to%20accept%20the%20money%20being%20concluded%20and%20is%20not%20dependent%20on%20the%20performance%20of%20the%20illegal%20promise%20by%20the%20receiver.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F06%2F18150923%2Fnarasimha-rao-cent-pti.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22760%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F06%2F18150923%2Fnarasimha-rao-cent-pti.jpeg%20760w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F06%2F18150923%2Fnarasimha-rao-cent-pti-300x175.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-535605%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22443%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENarasimha%20Rao.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ETwo-day%20hearing%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAppearing%20for%20Soren%2C%20Ramachandran%20argued%20against%20overruling%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EP.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eas%20in%20his%20view%2C%20it%20had%20stood%20the%20test%20of%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESubmitting%20that%20immunities%20are%20a%20distinct%20pillar%20in%20the%20constitutional%20edifice%20and%20as%20privileges%2C%20they%20ensure%20that%20members%20are%20not%20oppressed%20by%20the%20executive%2C%20Ramachandran%20argued%20that%20it%20is%20not%20for%20the%20court%20to%20find%20perfect%20solutions%20for%20all%20moral%20dilemmas%2C%20which%20are%20best%20left%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20parliament.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20attorney%20general%20R.%20Venkataramani%20distinguished%20between%20a%20Rajya%20Sabha%20election%20and%20a%20legislative%20vote%20and%20argued%20that%20immunity%20would%20not%20be%20attracted%20in%20the%20former.%20Ramachandran%2C%20however%2C%20disagreed%20with%20this%20view.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20the%20broader%20question%2C%20however%2C%20Venkataramani%20submitted%20that%20privileges%20could%20not%20be%20misused%20to%20dilute%20trust%20in%20representatives.%20He%20too%20doubted%20the%20correctness%20of%20the%20majority%20verdict%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EP.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20by%20suggesting%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnexus%E2%80%9D%20theory%20disregarded%20any%20antecedent%20criminal%20conduct%20occurring%20prior%20to%20the%20speech%20or%20the%20vote%20in%20the%20House.%20But%20he%20requested%20the%20bench%20to%20moderate%20the%20dissenting%20view%20in%20the%20judgment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20solicitor%20general%20Tushar%20Mehta%20also%20contended%20against%20the%20majority%20view%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EP.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20because%20it%20made%20the%20performance%20of%20a%20promise%20(vote%20or%20speech%20in%20the%20House%20in%20return%20for%20a%20bribe)%20contingent%20for%20granting%20immunity%20from%20criminal%20prosecution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20him%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F1558%2F1%2FA1988-49.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESection%207%20of%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Corruption%20Act%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20made%20the%20performance%20of%20a%20promise%20irrelevant%20to%20its%20application%2C%20and%20this%20was%20missed%20by%20the%20majority%20judges.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESenior%20advocate%20D.S.%20Patwalia%2C%20who%20argued%20as%20amicus%20curiae%2C%20defended%20the%20dissenting%20view%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EP.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EArguing%20on%20behalf%20of%20an%20intervenor%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Gopal%20Sankaranarayanan%20also%20doubted%20the%20precedent%20value%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EP.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20disagreed%20with%20the%20majority%20view%20in%20that%20judgment%20that%20immunity%20should%20be%20broadly%20construed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20him%2C%20the%20law%20could%20not%20have%20intended%20to%20grant%20immunity%20to%20someone%20who%20would%20be%20guilty%20on%20the%20streets%20but%20not%20in%20parliament%20for%20the%20same%20offence.%20He%20suggested%20that%20criminality%20would%20apply%20to%20an%20MP%E2%80%99s%20act%20of%20receiving%20a%20bribe%2C%20irrespective%20of%20whether%20the%20promised%20act%20was%20performed%20by%20them%20before%20or%20after%20receiving%20the%20bribe.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESenior%20advocate%20Vijay%20Hansaria%20disagreed%20with%20the%20view%20of%20the%20majority%20judges%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EP.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Egranting%20immunity%20to%20all%20sorts%20of%20offences%20because%20of%20the%20broad%20terms%20with%20which%20they%20construed%20the%20words%20%E2%80%9Cin%20respect%20of%E2%80%9D%20in%20Articles%20105(2)%20and%20194(2)%2C%20to%20justify%20a%20nexus%20with%20the%20vote%20or%20speech%20in%20parliament%20or%20an%20assembly.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInstead%2C%20he%20suggested%20that%20the%20words%20%E2%80%9Cin%20respect%20of%E2%80%9D%20should%20be%20construed%20as%20being%20applicable%20only%20to%20instances%20essential%20to%20the%20legislature.%20Any%20criminal%20act%20outside%20the%20House%2C%20committed%20by%20the%20members%2C%20would%20fall%20outside%20the%20cloak%20of%20immunity%2C%20irrespective%20of%20its%20nexus%20with%20the%20vote%20or%20speech%20in%20the%20legislature%2C%20he%20suggested.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20majority%20view%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EP.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20judgment%20also%20came%20under%20criticism%20from%20the%20counsel%20for%20ignoring%20voters%E2%80%99%20trust%20in%20their%20representatives%2C%20and%20for%20supporting%20the%20contention%20that%20parliamentarians%20deserved%20a%20higher%20pedestal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20referring%20to%20the%20correctness%20of%20the%20majority%20decision%20to%20a%20seven-judge%20bench%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20noted%20that%20it%20has%20serious%20ramifications%20for%20the%20polity%20and%20the%20preservation%20of%20probity%20in%20public%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696599901000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2F20172512%2F2022_5img20_May_2022_PTI05_20_2022_000129B-min.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Framesh-bidhuri-remarks-immunity-conspiracy-supreme-court%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20two-day%20hearing%20before%20the%20seven-judge%20constitution%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20the%20correctness%20of%20the%20previous%20judgment%20in%20P.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%20vs%20State%20(1998)%20concluded%20on%20Thursday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Framesh-bidhuri-remarks-immunity-conspiracy-supreme-court%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22TCS%20to%20consider%20buyback%20of%20shares%20in%20board%20meeti