Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBhubaneswar%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20passage%20of%20a%20controversial%20land%20acquisition%20Bill%20in%20late%20September%20by%20the%20Odisha%20assembly%20amidst%20a%20boycott%20by%20the%20opposition%20has%20evoked%20sharp%20reactions%20from%20major%20political%20parties%20and%20rights%20activists.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Right%20to%20Fair%20Compensation%20and%20Transparency%20in%20Land%20Acquisition%2C%20Rehabilitation%20and%20Resettlement%20(Odisha%20Amendment)%20Bill%20(RFCTLAR%26amp%3BR)%2C%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fother-states%2Fodisha-assembly-passes-bill-exempting-projects-from-social-impact-assessment%2Farticle67353558.ece%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Odisha%2520Legislative%2520Assembly%2520on%2Cimpact%2520assessment%2520(SIA)%2520and%2520special%5C%22%3Epassed%20on%20September%2027%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20empowers%20the%20government%20to%20exempt%20%E2%80%98strategic%20and%20development%20projects%E2%80%99%20from%20social%20impact%20assessment%20(SIA)%20and%20special%20provisions%20to%20ensure%20food%20security%20%E2%80%93%20which%20were%20hitherto%20considered%20mandatory.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20brute%20majority%20(114%20out%20of%20147%20seats)%20that%20the%20ruling%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%20(BJD)%20enjoys%20in%20the%20legislature%2C%20the%20Bill%20was%20passed%20without%20a%20hitch.%20But%20the%20opposition%20parties%20staged%20a%20walkout%20to%20register%20their%20protest.%20Making%20a%20statement%2C%20revenue%20and%20disaster%20management%20minister%20Sudam%20Marndi%20said%20that%20mandatory%20provisions%20in%20the%20RFCTLAR%26amp%3BR%20Bill%20like%20SIA%20and%20special%20provisions%20for%20food%20security%20were%20delaying%20the%20acquisition%20of%20land.%20The%20minister%20referred%20to%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20Make-In-Odisha%20conclaves%20aimed%20at%20attracting%20private%20investments%20in%20mega%20projects%20across%20sectors.%20Fast-tracking%20these%20projects%20depends%20a%20lot%20on%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20provide%20trouble-free%20land%20to%20the%20project%20proponents.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20Bill%20will%20enable%20the%20state%20government%20to%20issue%20notifications%20exempting%20projects%20vital%20to%20national%20security%20or%20defence%20and%20infrastructure%20development%20from%20SIA%20and%20food%20security%20provisions.%20Projects%20like%20affordable%20housing%2C%20industrial%20corridors%20set%20up%20by%20the%20state%20government%2C%20infrastructure%20projects%2C%20including%20highways%20and%20railways%2C%20and%20industrial%20projects%20involving%20displacement%20of%20100%20families%20or%20less%20or%20acquisition%20of%20private%20land%20of%20500%20acres%20or%20less%20will%20be%20exempted%20from%20conducting%20mandatory%20SIA.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Bill%2C%20the%20RFCTLAR%26amp%3BR%20Act%2C%202013%2C%20a%20central%20law%20which%20makes%20SIA%20mandatory%2C%20%E2%80%9Ccauses%20a%20delay%20in%20acquisition%20of%20land.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERights%20activist%20and%20leader%20of%20Lok%20Shakti%20Abhiyan%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fkidnapping-of-anti-mining-activist-samantara-casts-spotlight-on-bauxite-mining-protests-in-odisha%5C%22%3EPrafulla%20Samantara%3C%2Fa%3E%20lambasted%20the%20state%20government%20for%20bringing%20amending%20the%20Central%20law%20to%20facilitate%20the%20acquisition%20of%20land%20for%20various%20projects.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20new%20Bill%20goes%20against%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20Central%20law.%20It%20is%20anti-democratic%20and%20anti-people.%20It%20is%20now%20more%20than%20obvious%20that%20the%20government%20is%20on%20the%20side%20of%20the%20corporates%20without%20bothering%20about%20the%20plight%20of%20common%20people%2C%20especially%20the%20tiller%20of%20land%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Samatara%2C%20who%20is%20currently%20engaged%20in%20a%20fight%20for%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20land%20that%20a%20corporate%20house%20is%20trying%20to%20mine%20for%20bauxite%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fodishatv.in%2Fnews%2Fodisha%2Fresentment-erupts-over-vedanta-s-bauxite-mining-at-sijimali-in-odisha-214162%5C%22%3ESijimali%20area%20of%20Rayagada%20district%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20said%20that%20for%20land%20acquisition%2C%20not%20only%20the%20consent%20of%20the%20tiller%20of%20the%20land%20should%20be%20taken%20but%20also%20the%20opinion%20of%20the%20gram%20sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07210423%2Fimage-1298.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22890%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07210423%2Fimage-1298.png%20890w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07210423%2Fimage-1298-300x116.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671968%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22343%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrafulla%20Samantara.%20Photo%3A%20CC%20BY-SA%202.0%2FWikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3ELawyer-cum-activist%20Siddhartha%20Nayak%2C%20who%20was%20one%20of%20the%20leading%20lights%20of%20the%20movement%20against%20mining%20in%20the%20Niyamgiri%20hills%2C%20was%20also%20critical%20of%20the%20government.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20the%20most%20undemocratic%20step%20taken%20by%20the%20government%20for%20the%20acquisition%20of%20land.%20Its%20prime%20victims%20will%20be%20poor%20tribals%20who%20are%20fighting%20for%20their%20land%20rights%20in%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20state.%20We%20need%20to%20launch%20a%20state-wide%20movement%20to%20oppose%20this%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Nayak.%20He%20said%20the%20Bill%20is%20a%20sign%20of%20desperation%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20government%2C%20which%20has%20failed%20to%20acquire%20land%20peacefully%20for%20certain%20mega%20projects%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20ArcelorMittal%20pulled%20out%20of%20Odisha%20after%20scrapping%20its%20%2412%20billion%20(Rs%2050%2C000%20crore)%20steel%20plant%20project%20because%20of%20problems%20in%20acquiring%20land.%20This%20was%20a%20blow%20to%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20attempts%20to%20showcase%20investments%20in%20major%20projects%20as%20an%20achievement%20on%20the%20industrialisation%20front.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20the%20state%20government%20suffered%20another%20major%20blow%20when%20POSCO%2C%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20fourth-largest%20steelmaker%2C%20withdrew%20from%20its%2012-million-tonne-capacity%20steel%20project%20in%20Jagatsinghpur%20district.%20This%20was%20at%20that%20time%20considered%20to%20be%20the%20biggest%20foreign%20direct%20investment%20(FDI)%20in%20the%20steel%20sector%20in%20the%20country.%20However%2C%20the%20South%20Korean%20company%20had%20to%20retract%20because%20land%20acquisition%20for%20the%20project%20led%20to%20widespread%20violence%20at%20the%20project%20site.%20POSCO%E2%80%99s%20withdrawal%20also%20affected%20the%20ruling%20BJD%20politically.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fodisha-deja-vu-dhinkia-protest-jindal-steel-project-posco%5C%22%3EOdisha%3A%20D%C3%A9j%C3%A0%20Vu%20in%20Dhinkia%20as%20People%20Renew%20Protests%20Against%20Jindal%E2%80%99s%20Steel%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20such%20cases%20which%20create%20problems%20for%20the%20state%20government.%20The%20government%20wants%20to%20avoid%20such%20hurdles%20at%20any%20cost%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Nayak.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELingraj%20Azad%2C%20another%20tall%20leader%20of%20the%20Niyamgiri%20movement%2C%20described%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20latest%20move%20as%20disgraceful.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20like%20looting%20someone%E2%80%99s%20land%20without%20even%20seeking%20their%20opinion.%20There%20is%20no%20respect%20for%20public%20opinion%20now.%20There%20can%20be%20no%20development%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20people%20because%20the%20very%20purpose%20of%20development%20is%20to%20better%20the%20lives%20of%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Azad.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELawyer-cum-activist%20Siddhartha%20Nayak%20felt%20that%20by%20passing%20such%20laws%2C%20the%20government%20was%20actually%20inviting%20trouble%20for%20itself%20as%20there%20is%20bound%20to%20be%20resistance.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20have%20seen%20this%20in%20Niyamgiri%2C%20where%20they%20had%20once%20backed%20attempts%20at%20bauxite%20mining%20by%20a%20major%20corporate%20house%20which%20is%20now%20eyeing%20bauxite%20reserves%20in%20Sijimali.%20The%20government%20and%20the%20corporate%20house%20thought%20that%20the%20tribal%20people%20resisting%20mining%20in%20the%20Niyamgiri%20hills%20would%20back%20out.%20They%20also%20tried%20to%20divide%20them%20using%20various%20means.%20But%20ultimately%20the%20people%20won%20and%20Niyamgiri%20became%20a%20symbol%20of%20the%20fight%20for%20people%E2%80%99s%20right%20over%20their%20land%20and%20the%20natural%20resources%20bestowed%20upon%20them%20by%20God.%20This%20Bill%20will%20similarly%20provoke%20common%20people%20to%20fight%20attempts%20by%20big%20corporate%20houses%20to%20take%20away%20their%20land%20with%20the%20support%20of%20the%20government%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Nayak.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESenior%20Congress%20leader%20and%20former%20MLA%20Lalatendu%20Mohapatra%20described%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20Bill%20despite%20a%20boycott%20by%20the%20opposition%20parties%20as%20%E2%80%9Cunfortunate%E2%80%9D%20and%20a%20sign%20of%20growing%20intolerance%20on%20the%20part%20of%20powers%20that%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20state%20BJP%20general%20secretary%20Bhrigu%20Buxipatra%20said%20that%20the%20government%20may%20have%20to%20pay%20a%20heavy%20price%20for%20going%20against%20the%20will%20of%20the%20people%20and%20forcin