7B%22title%22%3A%22Tired%20of%20Kids%20Outgrowing%20Products%2C%204%20Parents%20Start%20Subscription%20Model%20for%20Cycles%2C%20Cribs%20%26amp%3B%20More%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20fleeting%2C%20magical%20journey%20of%20children%20growing%20up%2C%20their%20cherished%20clothes%20and%20toys%20hold%20a%20special%20place%20in%20their%20parents%E2%80%99%20hearts.%20From%20their%20little%20onesies%20to%20the%20colourful%20cribs%20and%20little%20bicycles%2C%20these%20inanimate%20objects%20become%20the%20holders%20of%20hundreds%20of%20cherished%20memories.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20as%20children%20grow%20up%20to%20become%20adults%2C%20their%20once-beloved%20possessions%20are%20often%20forgotten%2C%20stashed%20away%2C%20or%20cast%20aside.%20As%20time%20passes%20by%2C%20these%20tiny%20reminders%20lose%20their%20home%20and%20most%20end%20up%20in%20landfills.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20very%20bicycles%20and%20cribs%20that%20were%20once%20a%20source%20of%20joy%20end%20up%20in%20dump%20yards%20rotting%20away%20and%20adding%20to%20the%20never-ending%20circle%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F307659%2Fdr-priyadarshini-karve-pune-environmentalist-scientist-steam-stove-biochar-from-agrowaste%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epollution%3C%2Fa%3E.%20By%20the%20time%20most%20parents%20realise%20it%2C%20it%20becomes%20very%20difficult%20for%20them%20to%20rectify%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20similar%20realisation%20occurred%20to%2038-year-old%20Pruthvi%20Gowda%20when%20he%20became%20father%20to%20his%20baby%20boy.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20truth%20that%20no%20parent%20can%20deny%20is%20that%20kids%20grow%20out%20of%20things%20at%20a%20very%20fast%20rate.%20While%20we%20might%20pass%20down%20certain%20things%20to%20cousins%20and%20siblings%2C%20most%20of%20the%20kids%E2%80%99%20products%20end%20up%20in%20landfills%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20realisation%20later%20gave%20birth%20to%20Gro%20Club%20%E2%80%94%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F77487%2Fbengaluru-startup-eco-friendly-wedding-cards%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBengaluru-based%20startup%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20has%20created%20a%20circular%20economy%20by%20lending%20baby-use%20products%20on%20a%20subscription%20basis.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMaking%20memories%20while%20being%20sustainable%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3ELaunched%20in%20January%202022%2C%20and%20currently%20operable%20only%20in%20Bengaluru%2C%20the%20company%20has%20received%20an%20overwhelming%20response%20from%20parents%20dealing%20with%20similar%20issues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPruthvi%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20I%20have%20worked%20in%20the%20marketing%20industry%20for%20some%20time%2C%20I%20had%20always%20been%20interested%20in%20becoming%20an%20entrepreneur.%20Gro%20Club%20is%20a%20passion%20project%20as%20it%20marries%20both%20sustainability%20and%20entrepreneurship.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20idea%20of%20Gro%20Club%20brewed%2C%20Pruthvi%20turned%20towards%20his%20friends%20Hrishikesh%20H%20S%2C%20Roopesh%20Shah%20and%20Sapna%20M%20S%20for%20support.%20%E2%80%9CHrishikesh%20and%20I%20worked%20together%20on%20my%20previous%20venture%20too%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says%2C%20adding%20that%20this%20is%20his%20dream%20team.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFour%20of%20us%20are%20parents%20of%20kids%20between%205%20and%2014%20years%20of%20age.%20They%20could%20relate%20to%20the%20problem%20of%20them%20outgrowing%20things%20too.%20Apart%20from%20that%2C%20all%20of%20us%20believed%20that%20with%20our%20startup%2C%20we%20could%20pitch-in%20and%20reduce%20the%20mounting%20trash%20in%20the%20landfills%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETerming%20products%20such%20as%20bicycles%2C%20cribs%2C%20bunk%20